83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
HOUSE AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4127
By COMMITTEE ON HEALTH CARE
February 17
1 On page 2 of the printed bill, delete line 14 and insert:
2 “(b) ‘Prohibited entity’ means a nonprofit reproductive health care provider that:
3 “(A) Received more than $800,000 in Medicaid reimbursements in 2023; and
4 “(B) Is not eligible to receive federal Medicaid funds.”.
5 Delete lines 21 through 27 and insert:
6 “SECTION 7. (1) Section 6 of this 2026 Act becomes operative only if a state or federal
7 law, rule, regulation or other government action is enacted, adopted or taken that prohibits
8 a prohibited entity, as defined in section 2 of this 2026 Act, from maintaining enrollment in
9 the state medical assistance program.
10 “(2) If a state or federal law, rule, regulation or other government action described in
11 subsection (1) of this section is enacted, adopted or taken, section 6 of this 2026 Act becomes
12 operative on the effective date of that law, rule, regulation or other government action.
13 “(3) The Oregon Health Authority shall immediately notify the Legislative Counsel if a
14 state or federal law, rule, regulation or other government action described in subsection (1)
15 of this section is enacted, adopted or taken.”.
16
